{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01MRFRrZ5bh5ywcZoYLYZuuE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The root cause is clear: `aux_wrap` uses an **unprotected call** (`state.call`) for the wrapped function. When `error(23)` propagates out, the `state.ci` is left pointing to the inner function's CI instead of `aux_wrap`'s CI. The subsequent `set_top(state, 0)` uses this wrong CI, corrupting the stack. All operations after that — including `poscall` adjusting results — operate on garbage positions.\n\nThe fix: use `state.protected_call` so the CI is properly restored and TBC variables are closed on error, exactly matching how real `coroutine.resume`/`lua_resume` works in C-Lua."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1201,"cache_read_input_tokens":160863,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1201},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7b02f0cd-a42a-42b3-ada8-8c5d45862757","uuid":"afb680a2-59e0-4dd2-a9a2-a6a91bb43b39","request_id":"req_011CbBBxirttZPJS2DMPHqBk"}
