{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_014GjoU2AvrWAKuv1cn7ZzoE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Zero errors. The build is green.\n\n---\n\n**Root cause:** `aux_wrap` in `crates/lua-stdlib/src/coro_lib.rs` used `state.call(nargs, -1)` — an **unprotected call** — to run the wrapped coroutine function. When the function raised `error(23)`, the error propagated via `?` but left `state.ci` pointing at the inner function's `CallInfo` instead of `aux_wrap`'s. Every subsequent stack operation in `aux_wrap` (especially `set_top(state, 0)` and the result push) used the wrong stack base, corrupting the result position. Back in `poscall`, the 1 returned result landed at a garbage slot, and later a call instruction tried to invoke whatever happened to be at that slot — which was `Nil` — producing the spurious \"attempt to call a nil value\".\n\n**Fix:** Changed `state.call(nargs, -1)` to `state.protected_call(nargs, -1, 0)` in `aux_wrap`. A protected call restores `state.ci` to `aux_wrap`'s frame on error and runs `close_protected` to close TBC variables, exactly mirroring how real Lua's `lua_resume`/`coroutine.wrap` works internally.\n\n**After the fix:** The spurious nil-call crash is gone. The test now progresses further and fails with `stdin:1009: assertion failed!` — a proper assertion error from the test that verifies yields don't close TBC variables, which is a known limitation of the synchronous coroutine emulation (Phase E will fix it with real stackful coroutines)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4193,"cache_read_input_tokens":172475,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4193},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7b02f0cd-a42a-42b3-ada8-8c5d45862757","uuid":"85311a33-0941-4f44-85b2-af7f5df1a375","request_id":"req_011CbBCBb5hAgDP4fiqHCYSV"}
